# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: LifeInRahayal | Scene: LifeInRahayal2
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Early the next day, Sarah had finished her breakfast and quickly took out to the streets of the city."
    new "Early the next day, Sarah had finished her breakfast and quickly took out to the streets of the city."

    old "She had some money, and now a place to stay, but she knew she didn't really have all that much."
    new "She had some money, and now a place to stay, but she knew she didn't really have all that much."

    old "Her money would see her through for maybe a month at best."
    new "Her money would see her through for maybe a month at best."

    old "Enough to give her space to breathe, too little to simply sit and be idle."
    new "Enough to give her space to breathe, too little to simply sit and be idle."

    old "She had to make the most of her time here, and Sarah was eager not to waste a moment of it."
    new "She had to make the most of her time here, and Sarah was eager not to waste a moment of it."

    old "Though she had set out with a clear goal, it wasn't long before Sarah found herself starting to become distracted."
    new "Though she had set out with a clear goal, it wasn't long before Sarah found herself starting to become distracted."

    old "She had lived most of her life in the capital of Rosanna, which to her had appeared a large city."
    new "She had lived most of her life in the capital of Rosanna, which to her had appeared a large city."

    old "Then she had arrived in Lethram, which had appeared to her larger still."
    new "Then she had arrived in Lethram, which had appeared to her larger still."

    old "But as she walked over one of the great plaza's of the city of Rahayal, Sarah could not help but be in awe."
    new "But as she walked over one of the great plaza's of the city of Rahayal, Sarah could not help but be in awe."

    old "The city of Rahayal was like a vast mountain, which by virtue of perspective rendered all other things small."
    new "The city of Rahayal was like a vast mountain, which by virtue of perspective rendered all other things small."

    old "Never in her life could she have imagined a city of this size could exist."
    new "Never in her life could she have imagined a city of this size could exist."

    old "Everywhere she looked, swarms of people moved about in endless productivity."
    new "Everywhere she looked, swarms of people moved about in endless productivity."

    old "Off in the far distance, the city stretched on as far as she could see."
    new "Off in the far distance, the city stretched on as far as she could see."

    old "Massive monuments that would have put the castle of her youth to shame, towered up and cast long shadows."
    new "Massive monuments that would have put the castle of her youth to shame, towered up and cast long shadows."

    old "When Sarah tried to hold the whole of the city in her mind, it made her dizzy."
    new "When Sarah tried to hold the whole of the city in her mind, it made her dizzy."

    old "But above all, there was one object that always loomed larger than any other, and could be seen from virtually every direction."
    new "But above all, there was one object that always loomed larger than any other, and could be seen from virtually every direction."

    old "The Black Pyramid, home of the Eternal Court, where the rulers of the Empire gathered and laid their plans upon the world."
    new "The Black Pyramid, home of the Eternal Court, where the rulers of the Empire gathered and laid their plans upon the world."

    old "Though it seemed near to her, Sarah quickly realized it was an optical illusion."
    new "Though it seemed near to her, Sarah quickly realized it was an optical illusion."

    old "The thing was simply so enormous that it always appeared close."
    new "The thing was simply so enormous that it always appeared close."

    old "As much as it drew her own attention, it seemed to leave everyone else entirely unbothered, hardly worth a glance."
    new "As much as it drew her own attention, it seemed to leave everyone else entirely unbothered, hardly worth a glance."

    old "And as the day went on, Sarah realized she too was quickly becoming oblivious to the thing."
    new "And as the day went on, Sarah realized she too was quickly becoming oblivious to the thing."

    old "Less and less she found herself looking at it, until before long, she hardly considered the construct worth even a brief glance."
    new "Less and less she found herself looking at it, until before long, she hardly considered the construct worth even a brief glance."

    old "Still exploring the city, Sarah made her way through streets and crowds, taking in all the sights."
    new "Still exploring the city, Sarah made her way through streets and crowds, taking in all the sights."

    old "Though much of the city filled with awe, there was one element that forever troubled her."
    new "Though much of the city filled with awe, there was one element that forever troubled her."

    old "Slavery, banned in the Union Kingdoms for her home, was very much alive in Rahayal and the rest of the Mythran Empire."
    new "Slavery, banned in the Union Kingdoms for her home, was very much alive in Rahayal and the rest of the Mythran Empire."

    old "In fact, by most accounts, the majority of the inhabitants of both the city and the empire, were slaves."
    new "In fact, by most accounts, the majority of the inhabitants of both the city and the empire, were slaves."

    old "Sarah watched them, bound with metal, marked with symbols that she could not understand."
    new "Sarah watched them, bound with metal, marked with symbols that she could not understand."

    old "At first, she saw the worst of them."
    new "At first, she saw the worst of them."

    old "The young men and women, dragged about nearly naked in long chain gangs, going from one place to another."
    new "The young men and women, dragged about nearly naked in long chain gangs, going from one place to another."

    old "But soon, the more she paid attention, Sarah realized that the slavery ran deeper."
    new "But soon, the more she paid attention, Sarah realized that the slavery ran deeper."

    old "The man or woman that pulled the slaves along by chain, often also bore the markings of a slave."
    new "The man or woman that pulled the slaves along by chain, often also bore the markings of a slave."

    old "Soldiers. Merchants. Officials."
    new "Soldiers. Merchants. Officials."

    old "The slaves of this Empire came in every kind, both lowly and high."
    new "The slaves of this Empire came in every kind, both lowly and high."

    old "Sarah was watching a young woman following in the footsteps of what appeared to be her master."
    new "Sarah was watching a young woman following in the footsteps of what appeared to be her master."

    old "Her head turned low, she looked at Sarah for a brief moment, and their eyes met."
    new "Her head turned low, she looked at Sarah for a brief moment, and their eyes met."

    old "The moment passed as quickly as it occurred, yet Sarah was left startled by it."
    new "The moment passed as quickly as it occurred, yet Sarah was left startled by it."

    old "The girl had looked so much like herself, yet in her eyes, a hollowness."
    new "The girl had looked so much like herself, yet in her eyes, a hollowness."

    old "Everything in her life had taught her to be good. She knew that she had to save the girl."
    new "Everything in her life had taught her to be good. She knew that she had to save the girl."

    old "And yet, she equally knew that in this place, she was powerless."
    new "And yet, she equally knew that in this place, she was powerless."

    old "Not only could she do nothing to save the girl physically, the truth was that the law also sided with the slavers."
    new "Not only could she do nothing to save the girl physically, the truth was that the law also sided with the slavers."

    old "If Sarah did anything, at best, the guards would drag her away."
    new "If Sarah did anything, at best, the guards would drag her away."

    old "And so instead, Sarah stood only nailed to the ground, watching something evil unfold."
    new "And so instead, Sarah stood only nailed to the ground, watching something evil unfold."

    old "The girl dissapeared along with her master, turning down some street."
    new "The girl dissapeared along with her master, turning down some street."

    old "A voice broke snapped Sarah from her stunned condition."
    new "A voice broke snapped Sarah from her stunned condition."

    old "Official\" \"Work! Work!"
    new "Official\" \"Work! Work!"

    old "Sarah turned to look at the man shouting."
    new "Sarah turned to look at the man shouting."

    old "She saw a man, well dressed and seemingly full of confidence, shouting at the corner of a street."
    new "She saw a man, well dressed and seemingly full of confidence, shouting at the corner of a street."

    old "A small crowd of people was gathering."
    new "A small crowd of people was gathering."

    old "Sarah walked towards them."
    new "Sarah walked towards them."

    old "Official\" \"We're looking for workers, you got a pair of hands that work, we got work!"
    new "Official\" \"We're looking for workers, you got a pair of hands that work, we got work!"

    old "Sarah pressed through the crowd to get closer to the man."
    new "Sarah pressed through the crowd to get closer to the man."

    old "Slave\" \"I can work!"
    new "Slave\" \"I can work!"

    old "She heard a man, bound in iron, call out."
    new "She heard a man, bound in iron, call out."

    old "The official shook his head."
    new "The official shook his head."

    old "Official\" \"No slaves, not for this job. Freemen and Freewomen only."
    new "Official\" \"No slaves, not for this job. Freemen and Freewomen only."

    old "Woman\" \"What's the work?"
    new "Woman\" \"What's the work?"

    old "More voices called out, asking questions."
    new "More voices called out, asking questions."

    old "Official\" \"One at a time, please!"
    new "Official\" \"One at a time, please!"

    old "The crowd seemed to quiet down a bit."
    new "The crowd seemed to quiet down a bit."

    old "Official\" \"I'm looking for people able to do servant work. House cleaning, cooking, basic skills."
    new "Official\" \"I'm looking for people able to do servant work. House cleaning, cooking, basic skills."

    old "Sarah thought about it."
    new "Sarah thought about it."

    old "The truth was that her noble birth had shielded her from such hard work."
    new "The truth was that her noble birth had shielded her from such hard work."

    old "Then again, she did imagine she'd able to learn it quickly enough."
    new "Then again, she did imagine she'd able to learn it quickly enough."

    old "Man\" \"What's the catch?"
    new "Man\" \"What's the catch?"

    old "The official seemed to suddenly become nervous."
    new "The official seemed to suddenly become nervous."

    old "Official\" \"No catch at all. Fair work for fair pay!"
    new "Official\" \"No catch at all. Fair work for fair pay!"

    old "Woman\" \"Where?"
    new "Woman\" \"Where?"

    old "Official\" \"Where? What does that matter! A servant in one house is a servant in another, no?!"
    new "Official\" \"Where? What does that matter! A servant in one house is a servant in another, no?!"

    old "Official\" \"It shouldn't matter where!"
    new "Official\" \"It shouldn't matter where!"

    old "The crowd become more unruly, sensing that something was up."
    new "The crowd become more unruly, sensing that something was up."

    old "Before long, more were yelling, asking him where the work was."
    new "Before long, more were yelling, asking him where the work was."

    old "The official threw up hands hands."
    new "The official threw up hands hands."

    old "Official\" \"Fine!"
    new "Official\" \"Fine!"

    old "Official\" \"The positions open are for servants at the Estate of the honourable Gilead."
    new "Official\" \"The positions open are for servants at the Estate of the honourable Gilead."

    old "Hearing the last word, the crowd seemed to explode in yelling and cursing."
    new "Hearing the last word, the crowd seemed to explode in yelling and cursing."

    old "Instantly, Sarah saw that large numbers of people began to walk away."
    new "Instantly, Sarah saw that large numbers of people began to walk away."

    old "Those few that remained were mostly there to hurl a last few insults at the official, before they also left."
    new "Those few that remained were mostly there to hurl a last few insults at the official, before they also left."

    old "Sarah turned to one of the women that was walking away."
    new "Sarah turned to one of the women that was walking away."

    old "Why are you leaving?"
    new "Why are you leaving?"

    old "Woman\" \"Cause you'd be mad to be workin at that freak's Estate."
    new "Woman\" \"Cause you'd be mad to be workin at that freak's Estate."

    old "Mad? Why?"
    new "Mad? Why?"

    old "Woman\" \"Trust me, somethin twisted goes up on there."
    new "Woman\" \"Trust me, somethin twisted goes up on there."

    old "Woman\" \"Servants go missin and each week the tryin to sucker new fools workin there."
    new "Woman\" \"Servants go missin and each week the tryin to sucker new fools workin there."

    old "Woman\" \"You value your life, don't go there."
    new "Woman\" \"You value your life, don't go there."

    old "The woman pulled away from Sarah and stormed off."
    new "The woman pulled away from Sarah and stormed off."

    old "Sarah turned back to look at the official."
    new "Sarah turned back to look at the official."

    old "The large crowd had dwindled down to five people."
    new "The large crowd had dwindled down to five people."

    old "Two men, two women and herself."
    new "Two men, two women and herself."

    old "The official sighed."
    new "The official sighed."

    old "Official\" \"Well, forget about them. And don't believe the rumors they peddle either!"
    new "Official\" \"Well, forget about them. And don't believe the rumors they peddle either!"

    old "Man\" \"Rumors?"
    new "Man\" \"Rumors?"

    old "The official smiled."
    new "The official smiled."

    old "Official\" \"Nothing. Forget I said anything."
    new "Official\" \"Nothing. Forget I said anything."

    old "Official\" \"Instead, how about that job? If you can do a hard day's work, it's all yours! And the pay is very fair!"
    new "Official\" \"Instead, how about that job? If you can do a hard day's work, it's all yours! And the pay is very fair!"

    old "One by one, the men and the women stepped forward and began signing the working contracts."
    new "One by one, the men and the women stepped forward and began signing the working contracts."

    old "When the last of them had signed, the official suddenly pointed directly at Sarah."
    new "When the last of them had signed, the official suddenly pointed directly at Sarah."

    old "Official\" \"You there, girly."
    new "Official\" \"You there, girly."

    old "Official\" \"How about it? We got kitchen work as well, I promise it will pay well!"
    new "Official\" \"How about it? We got kitchen work as well, I promise it will pay well!"

    old "Take the servant job"
    new "Take the servant job"

    old "Sarah still got chills when she thought about the woman's warning."
    new "Sarah still got chills when she thought about the woman's warning."

    old "No thank you, I think I'll keep looking."
    new "No thank you, I think I'll keep looking."

    old "The official spat on the ground."
    new "The official spat on the ground."

    old "Official\" \"Fine, go ahead. See if anyone else will take you, but I won't be here when you come crawling back for a job!"
    new "Official\" \"Fine, go ahead. See if anyone else will take you, but I won't be here when you come crawling back for a job!"

    old "With that, the official gathered the others that had signed on for a job and walked away."
    new "With that, the official gathered the others that had signed on for a job and walked away."

    old "Sarah watched them leave, wondering if she had not perhaps made a mistake."
    new "Sarah watched them leave, wondering if she had not perhaps made a mistake."

    old "Would she really be able to find another job this easily?"
    new "Would she really be able to find another job this easily?"

